back when we started.

297
00:16:21,230 --> 00:16:21,920
200 beds.

298
00:16:25,560 --> 00:16:26,950
One bed.

299
00:16:27,710 --> 00:16:28,520
Impossible.

300
00:16:29,560 --> 00:16:31,040
When I first met Bu,

301
00:16:31,230 --> 00:16:33,040
he showed me the hospital's map.

302
00:16:33,280 --> 00:16:34,350
There were 200 beds.

303
00:16:34,750 --> 00:16:35,800
What he talked about

304
00:16:36,630 --> 00:16:39,110
was after Haicheng Hospital
has been established.

305
00:16:40,320 --> 00:16:42,350
I meant all the way at the start

306
00:16:43,920 --> 00:16:44,990
with one tent,

307
00:16:46,520 --> 00:16:47,520
one bed,

308
00:16:48,350 --> 00:16:49,680
and three doctors.

309
00:16:51,110 --> 00:16:51,830
Bu,

310
00:16:52,870 --> 00:16:53,560
Chen Miao,

311
00:16:54,920 --> 00:16:55,750
and me.

312
00:16:57,440 --> 00:16:59,400
They were my students.

313
00:17:00,750 --> 00:17:02,950
In the Great Floods of 1998,

314
00:17:03,720 --> 00:17:06,390
the three of us met in Haicheng.

315
00:17:08,190 --> 00:17:09,870
We rushed off

316
00:17:10,800 --> 00:17:12,280
to help with the floods.

317
00:17:15,280 --> 00:17:16,800
The tent was the hospital.

318
00:17:17,350 --> 00:17:19,390
The stretcher was our operating table.

319
00:17:20,760 --> 00:17:21,870
Back then,

320
00:17:22,280 --> 00:17:25,280
we wanted to build a hospital.

321
00:17:26,830 --> 00:17:28,480
That's why the hospital's logo

322
00:17:30,350 --> 00:17:32,110
is a tent.

323
00:17:41,150 --> 00:17:42,280
Do those three lines

324
00:17:42,670 --> 00:17:43,870
represent the three of you?

325
00:17:44,720 --> 00:17:45,240
No.

326
00:17:46,480 --> 00:17:47,830
The first line

327
00:17:48,560 --> 00:17:49,670
represents medical skills.

328
00:17:52,630 --> 00:17:55,000
Medical skills
are the foundation of medicine.

329
00:17:55,280 --> 00:17:56,480
The improvement of our skills

330
00:17:56,590 --> 00:17:58,870
means society, this big machine,

331
00:17:58,870 --> 00:18:00,760
will work better,

332
00:18:00,960 --> 00:18:03,150
driving forward humanity's development.

333
00:18:03,760 --> 00:18:04,910
The second line

334
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:07,240
represents medical ethics.

335
00:18:07,590 --> 00:18:09,910
The danger of doctors without ethics

336
00:18:10,190 --> 00:18:13,240
is greater than any illness.

337
00:18:13,960 --> 00:18:15,080
Like just now.

338
00:18:15,520 --> 00:18:17,830
If the patients lost their lives,

339
00:18:19,240 --> 00:18:21,630
it wouldn't be due to their illness,

340
00:18:21,830 --> 00:18:24,150
but due to the doctors

341
00:18:24,390 --> 00:18:27,480
who intentionally delayed operating.

342
00:18:37,110 --> 00:18:38,800
Skills, ethics,

343
00:18:39,560 --> 00:18:40,480
and what's the last one?

344
00:18:42,190 --> 00:18:43,040
The doctors and patients.

345
00:18:45,150 --> 00:18:45,960
The doctors and patients.

346
00:18:46,480 --> 00:18:47,800
Listen to that phrase.

347
00:18:49,150 --> 00:18:50,150
Doctors are in front,

348
00:18:50,870 --> 00:18:51,830
with the patients coming after.

349
00:18:53,480 --> 00:18:54,720
It's illogical.

350
00:18:55,430 --> 00:18:58,190
You must have patients
before you have doctors.

351
00:18:58,320 --> 00:19:00,080
In my opinion,

352
00:19:00,910 --> 00:19:02,830
it should represent
patients and doctors.

353
00:19:04,670 --> 00:19:06,960
Doctors who don't see patients

354
00:19:07,280 --> 00:19:09,350
aren't real doctors.

355
00:19:09,960 --> 00:19:12,480
Doctors have to look at the illness

356
00:19:12,910 --> 00:19:14,670
and the patient.

357
00:19:15,870 --> 00:19:17,720
It's only when we have a clear view

358
00:19:18,280 --> 00:19:19,800
of who the patients are

359
00:19:20,190 --> 00:19:22,320
can we better treat them.

360
00:19:23,350 --> 00:19:24,870
But we don't have a lot of time

361
00:19:25,190 --> 00:19:26,190
to get to know our patients.

362
00:19:26,760 --> 00:19:27,280
Yes.

363
00:19:27,720 --> 00:19:30,150
Our careers are so short,

364
00:19:30,670 --> 00:19:32,630
but the patients we treat

365
00:19:33,320 --> 00:19:34,800
are infinite in number.

366
00:19:35,560 --> 00:19:37,320
That is a fact,

367
00:19:38,350 --> 00:19:40,080
but it can't be the reason

368
00:19:40,190 --> 00:19:41,960
we run away from reality

369
00:19:44,560 --> 00:19:45,830
instead of changing it.

370
00:19:46,480 --> 00:19:50,080
